    """
    Cast the elements of an array to a given dtype in a nan-safe manner.

    Parameters
    ----------
    arr : array_like
        Input data.
    dtype : numpy.dtype or pandas.CategoricalDtype or str
        Data type to cast the elements of arr to.
    copy : bool, default True
        Whether to return a copy of arr. If False and no cast is necessary, return arr without copying.
    skipna: bool, default False
        Whether to convert NaN values in the array to the target dtype.

    Returns
    -------
    casted : ndarray
        An array with the same data as arr, but casted to the specified dtype.

    Raises
    ------
    TypeError
        If the data type cannot be cast to the desired dtype.

    Examples
    --------
    >>> df = pd.DataFrame({'A': [1, 2, 3], 'B': ['a', 'b', 'c']})
    >>> df['A'] = df['A'].astype('str')
    >>> df.dtypes
    A    object
    B    object
    dtype: object
